          <details class="faq-item reveal" name="faq-sm">
            <summary class="faq-q">Do you write all the captions?</summary>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Our team writes every caption including hooks, body copy, CTAs, and hashtags. You get a content calendar to review and approve before anything goes live — you're always in control.</p></div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item reveal" name="faq-sm">
            <summary class="faq-q">What platforms do you manage?</summary>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>We manage Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, LinkedIn, and Google Business. Most clients start with 1–2 platforms based on where their buyers are most active, then expand as results compound.</p></div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item reveal" name="faq-sm">
            <summary class="faq-q">How do you measure success?</summary>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>We track reach, engagement, follower growth, and direct attribution — meaning posts we can tie directly to leads and sales. Vanity metrics alone don't cut it. You'll see a clear monthly report on what's actually moving the needle.</p></div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item reveal" name="faq-sm">
            <summary class="faq-q">Do I need to be involved day-to-day?</summary>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>No — that's the whole point. You review and approve the monthly content calendar, then we handle everything else. Most clients spend less than an hour per month on social media after onboarding.</p></div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item reveal" name="faq-sm">
            <summary class="faq-q">How does High Tide Radar improve social media results?</summary>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>Radar identifies who in your specific market is actively looking to buy right now — by name and address. We build your content strategy around those people, so every post is targeting warm buyers instead of cold followers.</p></div>
